{
  "texts": [
    "By searching for relevant information from numerous documents, RAG enhances the generation process with the most recent and contextually relevant content [141].",
    "Additionally, RAG includes evidence-based information, increasing the reliability and credibility of LLM responses [139].To further enhance the reliability of LLM content and minimize hallucinations, recent studies suggest adjusting model parameters, such as the 'temperature' setting [142][143][144].",
    "The 'temperature' parameter influences the randomness and predictability of outputs [145].",
    "Lowering the temperature typically results in more deterministic outputs, enhancing coherence and reducing irrelevant content [146].",
    "However, this adjustment can also limit the model's creativity and adaptability, potentially making it less effective in scenarios requiring diverse or nuanced responses."
  ]
}